Step-by-step method details
For quantification of live cell ruffles, follow steps 1–15; for quantification of fixed cell ruffles, follow steps 16–22.
Live cell quantification: Initial image processing (optional)
Timing: 5–15 min
Here we outline the steps for initial processing of the data collected from before you begin[href=https://www.wicell.org#before-you-begin] steps 1–18. Initial image processing is performed in FIJI/ImageJ (see key resources table[href=https://www.wicell.org#key-resources-table] for download link). While image processing is not always necessary for analysis, it can make analysis easier and is highly recommended for display purposes. The following steps can be adapted as necessary as some may be unnecessary based on the quality of the image and/or the system used.
Drift/jitter correction: Often during live imaging there can be problems with drift if the system is not very stable (temperature or stage/dish stability).
To correct drift, run the FIJI/ImageJ plugin: Plugins › Registration › Correct 3D drift.
After drift/jitter correction, crop out the black bars around the stack by drawing a rectangular ROI and running Image › Crop.
Note: Jittering in the movies can occur during multi-point image acquisition, especially if the imaging regions are far apart. Both problems can be corrected using the Correct 3D drift plugin. The default settings work well in most scenarios, however, if processing speed is slow and/or the results are unsatisfactory, draw a rectangular region of interest (ROI) around a relatively unmoving part of the time series (e.g., a non-migratory cell) to calculate the stabilization on the contents of the ROI.
Background subtraction: The following background subtraction script can be run using the FIJI/ImageJ macro tool: Plugins › New › Macro.
waitForUser("Draw an ROI to indicate the background, then press OK");
for (i=1; i<=nSlices; i++) {
    setSlice(i);
    getStatistics(area, mean);
    run("Select None");
    run("Subtract...", "value="+mean);
    run("Restore Selection");
    }
run("Select None");
